Check if LAD of the local ancestry simulation match the expecedLAD in Zatlen et al.2017

#simulate 2 independent loci
#track (time, LAD, P, expectedLAD)
## t: number of generation
## LAD: covariance of local ancestry of 2 independent loci
## P: correlation of global ancestry of parents
## expectedLAD: expectedladr(0.5, P, 0, 0.5, t)
### recombination rate = 0.5, fraction of one of the ancestral population in the admixture event = 0.5, migration rate = 0

library(data.table)
LAD=function(seed, P){
  nloci = 2 #number of loci
  n = 1e4 #sample size
  t = 20 # number of generation
  set.seed(seed)
  # simulate global ancestry of parental meta groups
  ganc_meta = matrix(NA, nrow = t+1, ncol = n)
  ganc_meta[1,] = c(rep(1, (n/2)), rep(0, (n/2))) 
  # get parental global ancestry combination and calculate the ganc of admix pop
  corrthresh = 0.01 #correlation threshold
  for (i in 1:t){ #generation of admixture
    u = 100
    l = 0
    c = -2*corrthresh
    iter = 1
    clist = c
    # search for mate pairs to meet the P
    while(abs(c-P) > corrthresh){
      iter = iter + 1
      s = (u+l)/2
      #print(sprintf('c = %f s = %f P = %f iter = %d', c, s, P, iter))
      #sort the score and get the index of the sorted list
      idxm = sort(ganc_meta[i,]  + rnorm(n, 0, 1)*s, index.return=TRUE)$ix 
      idxf = sort(ganc_meta[i,]  + rnorm(n, 0, 1)*s, index.return=TRUE)$ix
      # correlation of ganc of mat and fat
      c = cor(ganc_meta[i,idxf], ganc_meta[i,idxm]) # get correlation of ganc
      clist[iter] = c # store the correlation
      if(c < P){ #adjust s to smaller value if c is smaller 
        u = s
      }else{ #adjust s to larger value if c is larger 
          l = s
          }
    }
    # calculate the global ancestry with the mate pairs
    # update the global ancestry pool in the metapop each round
    ganc_meta[i+1,] = (ganc_meta[i,idxf] + ganc_meta[i,idxm])/2
  }

  # initialize the matrix to store LAD
  lad = matrix(NA, nrow = t+1, ncol = 2)
    
  for (i in 1:(t+1)){
      ganc = ganc_meta[i,]
      # local ancestry per marker: 0/1 copies of pop1 ancestry
      lanc_adm <- matrix(rbinom(n*nloci, 1, ganc), nrow=n, ncol=nloci)
      # calculate covariance between loci in metapop (t=0) and admixed pop (t=t)
      lad[i,1]=i-1
      lad[i,2]=cov(lanc_adm[,1], lanc_adm[,2])
  }
return(lad)}



P3=LAD(1, 0.3)
P6=LAD(1, 0.6)
P9=LAD(1, 0.9)

# cbind different results
ladS1=cbind(P3, P6[,2], P9[,2])
colnames(ladS1)=c("Time", "LAD_P3", "LAD_P6", "LAD_P9")

# plot 
#read file of expected lad
explad=read.table("explad.txt", header = T, sep = ",")
# combine expected with lad file
ladS1_1=cbind(ladS1, explad)
#plot 2 lines together
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(ladS1_1, aes(x=Time)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = LAD_P3, colour = "LAD", linetype="P3")) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = P3, colour="expected LAD", linetype="P3")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = LAD_P6, colour = "LAD", linetype="P6")) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = P6, colour="expected LAD", linetype="P6")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = LAD_P9, colour = "LAD", linetype="P9")) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = P9, colour="expected LAD", linetype="P9")) +
  scale_colour_manual("", 
                      breaks = c("LAD", "expected LAD"),
                      values = c("darkred", "steelblue")) +
  scale_linetype_manual("", 
                      breaks = c("P3", "P6", "P9"),
                      values = c("dotted", "twodash", "solid")) +
  
  theme_classic() +
  xlab("Time since admixture") +
  ylab("LAD (r=0.5)")  + 
  theme(aspect.ratio = 1, legend.position = "bottom")

Replicate for different P

library(data.table)
repLAD = function(reptime, P){
  nloci = 2 #number of loci
  n = 1e4 #sample size
  t = 20 # number of generation
  corrthresh = 0.01 #correlation threshold for P
  # initialize the matrix to store LAD
  lad = matrix(NA, nrow = t+1, ncol = reptime+1)   
  for (seed in 1:reptime){
    set.seed(seed)
    # simulate global ancestry of parental meta groups
    ganc_meta = matrix(NA, nrow = t+1, ncol = n)
    ganc_meta[1,] = c(rep(1, (n/2)), rep(0, (n/2))) 
    # get parental global ancestry combination and calculate the ganc of admix pop
    
    for (i in 1:t){ #generation of admixture
      u = 100
      l = 0
      c = -2*corrthresh
      iter = 1
      clist = c
      # search for mate pairs to meet the P
      while(abs(c-P) > corrthresh){
        iter = iter + 1
        s = (u+l)/2
        #print(sprintf('c = %f s = %f P = %f iter = %d', c, s, P, iter))
        #sort the score and get the index of the sorted list
        idxm = sort(ganc_meta[i,]  + rnorm(n, 0, 1)*s, index.return=TRUE)$ix 
        idxf = sort(ganc_meta[i,]  + rnorm(n, 0, 1)*s, index.return=TRUE)$ix
        # correlation of ganc of mat and fat
        c = cor(ganc_meta[i,idxf], ganc_meta[i,idxm]) # get correlation of ganc
        clist[iter] = c # store the correlation
        if(c < P){ #adjust s to smaller value if c is smaller 
          u = s
        }else{ #adjust s to larger value if c is larger 
            l = s
            }
      }
      # calculate the global ancestry with the mate pairs
      # update the global ancestry pool in the metapop each round
      ganc_meta[i+1,] = (ganc_meta[i,idxf] + ganc_meta[i,idxm])/2
    }
  
    for (i in 1:(t+1)){
        ganc = ganc_meta[i,]
        # local ancestry per marker: 0/1 copies of pop1 ancestry
        lanc_adm <- matrix(rbinom(n*nloci, 1, ganc), nrow=n, ncol=nloci)
        # calculate covariance between loci in metapop (t=0) and admixed pop (t=t)
        lad[i,1]=i-1
        lad[i,seed+1]=cov(lanc_adm[,1], lanc_adm[,2])
    }
  }
  colnames(lad)=c("Time", (paste0(rep("rep", reptime), 1:reptime)))
  return(lad)
}

# plot replicated results
repplot=function(df, refcol, ylab){
  # melt data table
  melted = reshape2::melt(df, id="Time")
  melted = tail(melted, -21)
  colnames(melted)=c("Time", "rep", "LAD")
  melted$Time = melted$Time-1
  # plot
  ggplot() + 
    geom_line(data=melted, aes(x=Time, y=LAD, group=rep), color="darkred") + 
    geom_line(data=ladS1_1, aes(x=Time, y=refcol), color="steelblue") +
    theme_classic() +
    xlab("Time since admixture") +
    ylab(ylab)  + 
    theme(aspect.ratio = 1, legend.position = "bottom")
}


# plot
reptime = 20
repP3 = repLAD(reptime, 0.3)
repplot(repP3, ladS1_1$P3, ylab="LAD (r=0.5, P=0.3)")

repP6 = repLAD(reptime, 0.6)
repplot(repP6, ladS1_1$P6, ylab="LAD (r=0.5, P=0.6)")

repP9 = repLAD(reptime, 0.9)
repplot(repP9, ladS1_1$P9, ylab="LAD (r=0.5, P=0.9)")
